<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Simon, Julian L, "<a href="http://www.juliansimon.org/writings/Articles/REVOLUTI.txt" class="external text" title="http://www.juliansimon.org/writings/Articles/REVOLUTI.txt" rel="nofollow">More People, Greater Wealth, More Resources, Healthier Environment</a>", <i>Economic Affairs: J. Inst. Econ. Affairs</i>, April 1994.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Arrow, K., P. Dasgupta, L. Goulder, G. Daily, P. Ehrlich, G. Heal, S. Levin, K. Mäler, S. Schneider, D. Starrett and B. Walker, "Are We Consuming Too Much" <i>Journal of Economic Perspectives</i>, 18(3), 147-172, 2004.</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.fao.org/english/newsroom/news/2002/7828-en.html" class="external text" title="http://www.fao.org/english/newsroom/news/2002/7828-en.html" rel="nofollow">World agriculture 2030: Global food production will exceed population growth</a> August 20, 2002.</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://ptonline.aip.org/journals/doc/PHTOAD-ft/vol_57/iss_11/12_1.shtml" class="external text" title="http://ptonline.aip.org/journals/doc/PHTOAD-ft/vol_57/iss_11/12_1.shtml" rel="nofollow">Long−Term Energy Solutions: The Truth Behind the Silent Lie</a> November 2004</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> The Ultimate Resource II: People, Materials, and Environment in <a href="http://www.juliansimon.com/writings/Ultimate_Resource/" class="external free" title="http://www.juliansimon.com/writings/Ultimate_Resource/" rel="nofollow">http://www.juliansimon.com/writings/Ultimate_Resource/</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p>The Wanting Seed- Anthony Burgess</p>
